I";<p>I’m a science educator and director of science research at Riverdale Country School in The Bronx and an Adjunct Associate Research Scientist in the Department of Ecology, Evolution and Environmental Biology (E3B) at Columbia University in New York.
I oversee the activities of the Lisman Laboratory for Molecular Ecology at Riverdale Country School and advise students on summer research activities and internships. I help to organize the Riverdale’s annual Student Science Symposium and I co-lead field work, outdoor leadership, and science conference trips.</p>
